<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="fig_7"><head>Figure 3 :</head><label>3</label><figDesc>Figure 3: FC and ZFC magnetization (MT) of Nb 0.25 Bi 2 Se 3 single crystal from 1.5 to 5.5K at 20Oe applied field, the inset shows the isothermal magnetization (MH) of the same at 2, 2.2 and 2.4K.</figDesc></figure>
<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="table" xml:id="tab_0"><head></head><label></label><figDesc>curve for studied Nb 0.25 Bi 2 Se 3 crystal at 2, 2.2 and 2.4K i.e., below the critical temperature. The wide open MH plots confirm the observation of bulk superconductivity right up to 2.4K. The lower critical field H c1 is found to be 50Oe and upper critical field H c2 being 900Oe at 2K. The same are 8.25Oe and 400Oe at 2.2K and 7.10Oe and 200Oe at 2.4K.</figDesc><table /></figure>
